When I work on AngularJS projects,
I usually start by cloning a template from Github:

%br/
%br/

%a(href='/posts/lineman_angular_install') lineman_angular_install

%br/
%br/

After I setup that template, in folder /tmp/latapp/
I should be able to 
see something like this:

%br/
%br/
%img(src='/images/lineman_angular_install1.png')
%br/

Once I see that page, I am confident that I have installed a Lineman Angular Template on my Ubuntu host.

%br/
%br/

The next step for me is to mix this template with coffeescript.

%br/
%br/

I enhance this file:

%pre
  %code /tmp/latapp/config/application.js

I place this syntax in application.js:

%pre
  =render 'lineman_angular_coffee1'

After I verify that the app still behaves,
I install a module named js2coffee which is useful
for transforming a JavaScript file into a CoffeeScript file:

%pre
  %code npm i -g js2coffee

Next, I convert one of the JavaScript files into a CoffeeScript file:

%pre
  %code
    cd /tmp/latapp/app/js/
    js2coffee router.js > router.coffee
    mv router.js /tmp/

Again, I verify that the app still behaves.

